reviews.text: So much to see. I imagine the next time I am there I will see things I missed the first time around. Wonderfully displayed. There is a research broom which I am anxious to check out someday soon!
Wonderful view of local history.
Great old town
Amazing!!

Just the right size for the price & time. We really thought it was very interesting and beautiful. I wish I would have known about it sooner. I will definitely go again. Staff was very friendly and knowledgeable too & souvenirs very reasonable!
If you like antiques, music and mechanical devices this is the place for you!
A nice music museum also sells children's musical instruments like rhythm sticks and tambourines
Had excellent collection  the patrons and the guide were very informative.  Place was very well organized
Unique place to visit with a lot of history inside. Very interesting!

We went bowling which was enjoyable and has air hockey tables, pool tables and various other games. There are lots of restaurants and a trampoline attraction which we will be trying soon, there is a private health care clinic also. Can easy spend about 4-5 hours here. Easy accessible by a good choice of buses. Underground parking also.

This is not a shopping area. Decent cinema, usually busy. Now got better restaurants. Crazy golf, arcade area and bowling which also has their own arcade and pool area too. Excellent parking and free if you're using their services. Large casino which is usually busy. There is also softplay but is expensive. Something to do for everyone apart from shopping.

As a teenager I go out a lot with my friends. Fountain Park is a great place to have fun and just hang out.

There are many places to eat and many cater towards my vegan diet especially Pizza Hut.

The cinema is really good and I go there all the time. I would definately recommend.

There is also a fun zone but I wouldnt recommend staying there too long because all the lights and sounds gave me a headache.

An easy place to get to Cineworld and there's some good food options if you're into the chain places. I like it because it has the bowling, pool and arcade complex on the right but that's not for everyone
Great game of miniature golf. We were on a works day out and we all had a game. Very competitive.
Great food! There homemade bread is second to none! If you like Italian food this is the place to go!
They have awesome Alfredo linguini broccoli, chicken, or nothing on it, its just amazing. They also serve delicious Wine bottled or in a glass so an awesome place for a date with a special somebody😄
I can remember my grandmother taking me there when a was jus a youngster! Its def the best Italian restaurant! My dad loved their subs!!!
Love going back to a hometown restaurant. Leo’s never fails to provide a yummy meal. Most takeout friendly establishments don’t make it to my contact list, Leonardo’s is an exception.

The food here can only be described as great! Anything you want that’s Italian is probably on the menu plus some things you’ve probably never heard of. My personal pick is the calzones, which reminds me, the portions are huge here. It’s likely that if you’re going to have any of the bread that they serve as a precursor to your meal, and/or a salad, I would recommend just getting a half size when available. On the other hand however, what’s wrong with taking some of this wonderful food home with you? The staff is also polite to those they are waiting on. The atmosphere is good with lighting that feels warm and cozy along with the layout of the restaurant making you feel separate from the outside world, which is a nice touch. You’ll have to wait a little bit longer for your food, but I think it’s definitely worth it.

Wear your fancy pants or let your hair down this little spot offers atmosphere, friendly service and food that is outstanding! If you are from out of town or a local this place is a must! I have to recommend the Southern Breakfast Chop!! The balance of sweet and savory was perfect!
The staff is excellent, they all work together to service the customers table. The food is always good. It is definitely the "best place in town"!

Bella's is one of my all time favorite restaurants. The wait staff are always super attentive and friendly. Their ever evolving menu is sure to offer a high quality meal for everyone! Be sure to save room for dessert. The creme brulee is possibly the best I've ever had!

We had first-class service and first-class food. The salads, dressing, bread, crackers, soup, entrees were superb. I had the pecan-crusted chicken. Excellent. Pinto noir was excellent. Looking forward to a return visit. Quite a find in the heart of downtown Franklin.

I made reservations, for 5:30.  When our group of 4 arrived they couldn't find our reservations. So they made room for 2 at the bar.  Finally got seated 6:30.  We wolfed down our food, so we could make the play.
Food was good!
Amazing sandwiches for lunch. I have not been there for dinner though i plan on going soon. The food is fresh and healthy while still amazingly delicious. Go here if you get the chance.
Great little place. Awesome sandwiches. Dinner looks good but haven't tried it yet. Service is a little slow, especially with bussing of tables but generally worth it.
Cafe is under new ownership with a new chef and just expanded their menu along with extending their hours.  It is a great place to grab a bite!
Not bad.

Horrible maintenance the management will spread your personal business to other tenants. They also play favorites and only enforce the rules if its someone they dont like whom is causing the problem. Takes months to get stuff fixed.

We placed an order last night for 2 orders of bbq wings two orders of garlic wings one order of mild wings and a cheese pizza and a pepperoni pizza. We were told the food would be here in about 45 min to an hour. 
Two hours after placing the order it finally showed up. The wings were a soggy nasty mess that was only part covered in sauce and they were cold. 
The Pizza’s were also cold and the doe had large lumps all over that seemed under cooked. There was so much sauce on the pizzas that it could have just been soggy but the dough had stretch but the cheese would just slide off in chunks. 
We have ordered from them in the past and only had an issue one other time but figured it was just a screw up it happens this time I just can’t look past it. 
I won’t ever order from them again
Great service. Great prices.
Great hot sausage for the money
The prices are reasonable and the food is great
Gluten free pizza was delicious!
